      • addAllAbsent

        int addAllAbsent(Collection<? extends E> c)
        Adds all of the elements in the specified collection that are not already contained in this bag.
        Parameters:
        c - the collection containing elements to be added to this bag.
        Returns:
        the number of elements added.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the given collection is null or if it contains a null reference and this bag does not accept null elements.

      • addIfAbsent

        boolean addIfAbsent(E e)
        Adds the given element to this bag if not already present.
        Parameters:
        e - the element to be added to this bag, if absent.
        Returns:
        true if the element has been added.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if e is null and this bag does not accept null elements.
